</p>

</div>
<div id="fn" class="footnote"><a class="note-ref" href="#GEWN-02-09-02-0218-fn-0001-ptr" id="GEWN-02-09-02-0218-fn-0001">1</a>

   <p>Letter not found.</p>

</div>
<div class="footnote"><a class="note-ref" href="#GEWN-02-09-02-0218-fn-0002-ptr" id="GEWN-02-09-02-0218-fn-0002">2</a>

   <p>Simpson is attributing the worthlessness of GWs slave London to the loss of his toes to frostbite and to the worthlessness Natural in his bones. See <a href="default.xqy?keys=GEWN-print-02-09-02-0141" class="document">GW to Simpson, 23 February</a>.</p>

</div>
<div class="footnote"><a class="note-ref" href="#GEWN-02-09-02-0218-fn-0003-ptr" id="GEWN-02-09-02-0218-fn-0003">3</a>

   <p>Lit may be lead, meaning to carry on.</p>

</div>
<div class="footnote"><a class="note-ref" href="#GEWN-02-09-02-0218-fn-0004-ptr" id="GEWN-02-09-02-0218-fn-0004">4</a>

   <p>That is, from the start.</p>

</div>
<div class="footnote"><a class="note-ref" href="#GEWN-02-09-02-0218-fn-0005-ptr" id="GEWN-02-09-02-0218-fn-0005">5</a>

   <p>Richard Stogdon has not been identified.</p>

</div>
<div class="footnote"><a class="note-ref" href="#GEWN-02-09-02-0218-fn-0006-ptr" id="GEWN-02-09-02-0218-fn-0006">6</a>

   <p>For the partnership between Simpson and GW, see <a href="default.xqy?keys=GEWN-print-02-09-02-0082&amp;expandNote=GEWN-02-09-02-0082-sn#GEWN-02-09-02-0082-sn" class="document">Simpson to GW, 5 Oct. 1772, source note</a>.</p>

